Absor has been so wrong so often...<br>
Not a question of him being obtuse, just that EQ is so complex considering the tangled soup of the coding due to many upgrades and turn over in designers, it seems the left hand never knows what the right hand is doing.<br>
<br>
I've *seen* MS pets gangbang mobs, mobs die FAST.<br>
I've also seen occassions when charmed pets wont attack a target, and very rarely with normal pets as well on raids.<br>
In the first case the 4 NPC rule may have applied, in the second I have no idea what happened because with tons of pets on a mob there has been no problem, but once in a rare while it just glitches regardless of amount of pets.<br>
<br>
There IS coding that makes ordinary NPCs only hit 1 pc 4 per target. Pets got changed ages ago to not take rain waves, which changed them from being NORMAL npcs, thats when their proc rate got busted cause they werent normal NPCs anymore.<br>
<br>
If mobs are dying very fast with just a ton of pets on them, it CANNOT be 4 taking turns hitting because mobs regen etc would keep up with it, they'd die slow.<br>
Also you can see when the 4 NPC thing is in effect mobs go to attack, then turn away from target before closing.<br>
Put it this way, when the mass pet bug was in effect, I saw pets shred mobs in the Grey in like 10 seconds, it was hysterical. Or the case of, I think it was a necro, who took out all of Skyfire with 50+ pets....<br>
<br>
To test this why not use the Arena in Bazaar, get a tank hp buffed, send a ton of lower lvl pets on him, keep HITS MISSES on, see the if the amount of attacks changes when you add pets?<br>
<br>
