<br>
We brought more people up and bridged then to isle 6 tonight which brought our numbers to 42 (7 full groups).  I believe our magician count was at 26 tonight as we brought two extras.  I played my Enchanter for part of the round but moreso on pre-buffing and CR support since I was the only one there.<br>
<br>
We got the first pull from the bee on the right -- the monk puller had a graphics booboo and got _three_ bees at once.  With no ENC loaded (I was on as Symfyre), we proceeded to follow MA and /assist all of our troops.  We dropped several bees but we wound up killing the wrong bee set and within 5 minutes of the Braveheart fighting, the mini-boss named Bzzzt spawned.  This caused some problems as we had a a loss of several people up front.  There was also the mention of some sort of rare bee spawn that hit for 1200pts and killed a few of us.  With our numbers down, we killed Bzzzt and then Bazzt Bzzzt (big huge heavy bixie w/ huge pecs, L63 with a billion^6 hit points) spawned.  She proceeced to pick us off one by one with DT.  We had a serious wipeout and then a 1 and a half hour CR afterwards (had to wait for her to despawn as she was sitting right above all of our corpses, ugh) even though we got her down to half of the 'B' in her name, meaning she had about 2% of her health left.  We were _THIS_ close to doing it on the first round but failed.  With the despawning of the boss, there was no chance of getting a Sirran the Lunatic to spawn to let our necro turn in key to bump us to isle 7.  So, with that, we rezzed up, got up to mana, and parked it for the night.  We're going to try it again tomorrow and take what we've learned as well as take advantage of the spawn time if the island is still empty when we get back tomorrow.   We feel quite confident that we can do this.  We had to learn a few lessons including properly pulling, tagging, and assisting off the mob as well as the order and preparation in doing it all.  I think we can nail this one tomorrow night.  We're even more determined now than we were after seeing that we nearly had the main boss mob dead on the first strike.  20 more seconds and she would've been Gabobn fodder.<br>
